{
  "stem": "9262.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "So they knew that these, most likely, were German Jews, because German Jews had already arrived in '41.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "When we finished our schooling, we were told that our classes are going to be taken over for quarters of the Jews who will be coming from Germany, from Czechoslovakia, and from Austria and Luxembourg.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "So it was the end of the school and we were already all working.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "So that was in '42.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Now, my mother hid my little brother under the bed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And he wasn't found.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Then, when the Germans left our courtyard, and everything was all right, and we had to go back to our quarters, one of the Jewish militiamen came back, looked under the bed, and found my little brother, and forced to take him out.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And my mother was fighting with him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And she wouldn't let go of my little brother's hand.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "So he took her as well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And we looked out of our window and she was already sitting on the lorry.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And she waved to us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And she says, go back, go back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And she had my little brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were being deported.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know, at the time, where you-- where they were going.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's only when we went to Auschwitz we were told by others that all these transports who went from Lodz, at that time, were sent to Chelmno, which was not far-- about 40 kilometers away from Lodz-- and there they were gassed, in these gas vans.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they didn't have the proper gas ovens and the crematoria.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were burned in pits.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That what we were told from eye witnesses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I lost my mother and my brother-- my little brother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was just there with my older brother.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
